{"id":14881680,"mediaExerciseId":"e1e3e8be-b0eb-4986-bd1f-91c8c55c09f4","exerciseName":"3","chapterName":"19","chapterTitle":"Cash and Liquidity Management","groupId":612447,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":660,"solutions":[{"id":6005685,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we need to answer the question.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/12d16a14b1a1003796f664cffb1e4e00/172c798de108ffd425fe02b955851869/lateximg_large.png","width":645},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/12d16a14b1a1003796f664cffb1e4e00/172c798de108ffd425fe02b955851869/lateximg.png","width":322}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**a)**\nThe company's float is the product of average monthly checks received and the average number of days for the checks to clear, so \n$$\\begin{align*}\n\\text{Company float}&=\\text{Average monthly checks received}\\cdot \\text{Clearing time for the checks}\\\\\n&=\\$17,500\\cdot 3\\\\\n&=\\$52,500\n\\end{align*}$$\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"**b)** The largest amount of money that Purple Feet Wine would have to pay today to eliminate its float is the product of company float and annual interest rates. So,\n$$\\begin{align*}\n\\text{The highest amount }&=\\$52,500\\cdot(0.017\\cdot360)\\%\\\\\n&=\\$52,500\\cdot6.12\\%\\\\\n&=\\$52,500\\cdot 0.0612\\\\\n&=\\$3,213\n\\end{align*}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"**c)**  Maximum daily charge the company should be willing to pay to eliminate\nits float entirely is \n$$\\begin{align*}\n\\text{Maximum daily charge}&=\\text{Company float}\\cdot \\text{Daily interest rate}\\\\\n&=\\$52,500\\cdot0.017\\%\\\\\n&=\\frac{\\$52,500\\cdot0.017}{100} \\\\\n&=\\frac{\\$892.5}{100}\\\\\n&=\\$8.925\n\\end{align*}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"7e98fc1e-d515-4dbf-9065-3860023e7633","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881681,"exerciseName":"4","page":660,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"74bddda9-a8dc-4190-b134-ed83d33c34de","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-19-questions-and-problems-4-74bddda9-a8dc-4190-b134-ed83d33c34de"},{"id":14881682,"exerciseName":"5","page":660,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"18613fc7-b3dc-44f5-843d-3d90dfaa4ee2","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-19-questions-and-problems-5-18613fc7-b3dc-44f5-843d-3d90dfaa4ee2"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881679,"exerciseName":"2","page":660,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"d9442cba-bc68-4d0f-8627-be2bdf0d9162","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/f